The COVID-19 Education Crisis Committee says government’s push to reopen schools is deadly. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - Shut down schools and promote pupils to the next grades. That’s the call from the COVID-19 Education Crisis Committee, formed by concerned parents and communities. They say no country has successfully fought the coronavirus by opening schools when infections are rising. READ: Private schools hit in the pocket Following a week’s break, Grade 12 pupils are back in class, while other grades will be phased in from this coming week. The committee says it will continue to mobilise and intensify its protest action against the reopening of schools. - Coronavirus Hotline Number: 0800 029 999 from 8 am to 4 pm, Monday to Friday. Help protect your loved ones by sharing this official South African government COVID-19 service with your family, friends and community. Send HI to 0600 123 456 on WhatsApp. The NICD has another Clinician Hotline to improve #COVID19 communication and support for healthcare providers. The Clinician Hotline is 0800 11 1131, operating 24 hrs. The Public Hotline is 0800 029 999 also operating 24hrs.